"Vautard R., Hauglustaine D.","Impact of global climate change on regional air quality: Introduction to the thematic issue",2007,"Comptes Rendus - Geoscience","339","11-12",,"703","708",,,10.1016/j.crte.2007.08.012,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-36049009112&partnerID=40&md5=42e7d30ee3ce7c762c55ab624c411f83","Laboratoire des sciences du climat et de l'environnement (LSCE/IPSL), laboratoire CEA/CNRS/université de Versailles-Saint-Quentin, L'Orme des Merisiers, 91191 Gif-sur-Yvette, France","Vautard, R., Laboratoire des sciences du climat et de l'environnement (LSCE/IPSL), laboratoire CEA/CNRS/université de Versailles-Saint-Quentin, L'Orme des Merisiers, 91191 Gif-sur-Yvette, France; Hauglustaine, D., Laboratoire des sciences du climat et de l'environnement (LSCE/IPSL), laboratoire CEA/CNRS/université de Versailles-Saint-Quentin, L'Orme des Merisiers, 91191 Gif-sur-Yvette, France","Despite the major international efforts devoted to the understanding and to the future estimate of global climate change and its impact on regional scale processes, the evolution of the atmospheric composition in a changing climate is far to be understood. In particular, the future evolution of the concentration of near-surface pollutants determining air quality at a scale affecting human health and ecosystems is a subject of intense scientific research. This thematic issue reviews the current scientific knowledge of the consequences of global climate change on regional air quality and its related impact on the biosphere and on human mortality. This article provides a presentation of the key issues, summarizes the current knowledge, and introduces the thematic issue. © 2007 Académie des sciences.","Air quality; Climate change","air quality; atmospheric pollution; climate effect; concentration (composition); ecosystem response; estimation method; global change; health impact; regional climate",,,,,,"Brasseur, G.-P., Schultz, M., Granier, C., Saunois, M., Diehl, T., Botzet